verbs.description: upboost (third-person singular simple present upboosts, present participle upboosting, simple past and past participle upboosted)

examples: A few boostings are percieved[sic] as upboostings, but are realized in such a way that the auditively upboosted syllable is placed below the surrounding stressed syllables, and acoustically looks more like a downboosting, see fig. 11.
